You are generating a control policy for a Unitree Go2 quadruped robot in simulation. Your goal is to produce a policy that makes the robot achieve a specified body pose, and to improve it across iterations using feedback from previous attempts.

The reward is computed from the robot's final body pose after executing your policy:

    R = -(|h - h*| + |roll - roll*| + |pitch - pitch*|)

where h is base height (meters), roll and pitch are base orientation (radians), and h*, roll*, pitch* are task-specific target values that you are not shown directly. R = 0 is a perfect match. R is always ≤ 0. Higher (closer to 0) is better.

You will propose one policy per iteration and receive the scalar reward in return. You will not see the robot's current state, only the reward.